Because ids cannot contain a forward-slash it will be rewritten by rails helpers to an underscore. So the javascript could not replace the placeholders anymore.

Fixed proximal interface in glm.  There was a bug in intercept adjustment for data normalization of the w-given (prior coefficients)  was multiplying by normMul (1/sd(x)) instead of normSub (mean(x)) and was adding instead of subtracting to the intercept.
Fixed some more bugs and reverted back to using Jama Cholesky

1. Fix in recent rollup stats cleanup. Update rollups in DKV if computing hits and histo is needed (e.g. uuid col) (was hitting infinite loop)  2. Fix in KeySnapshot code - replaced frame.vecs().length with frame.numCols() call -> vecs() can be fetching keys which would throw assertion error since we're already running at GetKey priority level.
fix HTTP/2 encode error in case the status code was not one of 200 204 206 304 400 404 500
Merge pull request #186 from h2o/kazuho/issues/185  [http2] fix assertion failure in hpack encoder

fix `bytes_read` becoming incorrect when response is not received at once  The bug leads to internal state corruption as it may set `h2o_socket_buffer_prototype._initial_buf.size` to a non-zero value (happens when the HTTP response from upstream is received in multiple number of packets  and if the last packet did not contain any response body)
Fix a bug preventing multiple iterations of alternating minimization. Update R call to GLRM so comparable to built in PCA.
[bugfix] fix HPACK compressor output in case header is longer than 126 bytes
Merge pull request #193 from h2o/kazuho/issues/192  fix HPACK compressor output in case header is longer than 126 bytes
Fix a leaked key bug and incorrect calculation of objective function

GLM bug fix.  Response prior (if different from actual mean) was rewriting internal lastResult variable used during line search. Datasets which require line search in the first iteration then used wrong intercept and line search would often fail to progress (and glm would return just the null model). Added clone() to prevent array sharing between the model coefficients and lastResult variable.
Bug fix in beta_constraints. domain of the names vec can be larger than the number of actual values  loop over the length of the vector instead of the size of the domain.
fixed a bug
Fix bug in as.h2o. h2o.exec call (for turning cols into enums) was somehow overwriting h2odataset object in outer scope. replaced h2o.exec call with simple as.factor.

Fix for PUBDEV-305. Output single error message listing all categorical columns when validating kmeans training frame

bugfix in integer quantiles  Bins for integer columns with a narrow range (<1024) are exact  and should report exact answers.  Was rounding bins "as if" the full 1024 bins were made  even for tiny ranges  leading to large roundoff errors in the quantile values.

fix bug in glm.  Predictors are expected to remain active once selected even though they may appear and then disappear from the model and may be filtered out by strong rules (This is to avoid problems with line search). This rule was broken once all columns were active and caused AIIOB.
Bug fix in glm to protect againts (throw IAE) user supplying beta_given but no vector of penalties in the beta_constraints.

Fix bugs with doing scoreMSE in double vs float precision  Since histograms in float precision (for space)  need to score in float precision as well  or else suffer 1 FP ULP differences in DP leading to junk tree splits (attempting to split 1 FP ULP but predictions are equal)
Fix bug with junk levels & cols  Scoring set might have more levels than the model (these extra levels are never predicted)  or extra cols.

Update documentation and Script examples to solve problem with default imports in Spark shell.  In Spark 1.5 Spark shell by default imports function called `hex` which causes problems in importing classes from H2O's hex package (for example  `import hex.tree.gbm.GBM`).  The solution is to reference top-level package via `_root_` reference: `import _root_.hex.tree.gbm.GBM`

f2fs: fix small discards not to issue redundantly  The ckpt_valid_map and cur_valid_map are synced by seg_info_to_raw_sit.  In the case of small discards  the candidates are selected before sync  while fitrim selects candidates after sync.  So  for small discards  we need to add candidates only just being obsoleted. mm/mempolicy.c: fix error handling in set_mempolicy and mbind.  In the case that compat_get_bitmap fails we do not want to copy the bitmap to the user as it will contain uninitialized stack data and leak sensitive data.  Change-Id: I54d1d5eb4712048f9148423a5430404804bfa474 Signed-off-by: Chris Salls <salls@cs.ucsb.edu> Signed-off-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>

input: misc: fix heap overflow issue in hbtp_input.c  Add the boundary check for ABS code before setting ABS params  to avoid heap overflow.  Bug: 32341680 CRs-fixed: 1096301 Change-Id: I6aad9916c92d2f775632406374dbb803063148de Signed-off-by: Vevek Venkatesan <vevekv@codeaurora.org> Signed-off-by: Dennis Cagle <d-cagle@codeaurora.org>

msm: crypto: fix issues on digest buf and copy_from_user in qcedev.c  Make the digest length not larger than the size of the buffer qcedev_areq.sha_op_req.digest; and use the checked variants of the copy_from/to_user() APIs to avoid small race window of their unchecked variants.  Change-Id: I3db0c20ac5fa47ed278f3d60368c406f472430c1 Signed-off-by: Zhen Kong <zkong@codeaurora.org>

BACKPORT: trace: resolve stack corruption due to string copy  Strcpy has no limit on string being copied which causes stack corruption leading to kernel panic. Use strlcpy to resolve the issue by providing length of string to be copied.  CRs-fixed: 1048480 Bug: 35399704 Change-Id: Ib290b25f7e0ff96927b8530e5c078869441d409f Signed-off-by: Amey Telawane <ameyt@codeaurora.org>

ASoC: msm: qdsp6v2: return error when copy from userspace fails  A copy_from_user is not always expected to succeed. Therefore  check for an error before operating on the buffer post copy.  Change-Id: Ibba9a47c84e735d30e32eeac5b80d51044b7a9e8 CRs-Fixed: 1094852 Signed-off-by: Siena Richard <sienar@codeaurora.org>

input: touchscreen: gt9xx: fix memory corruption in Goodix driver  Fix memory corruption in Goodix touchscreen driver  by resetting the global structure cmd_head to zero (except *data and wr flag) in goodix_tool_write handler on error case.  Change-Id: I4f7f8f464b93571627b922b10c10a65826228e42 Signed-off-by: Vevek Venkatesan <vevekv@codeaurora.org>
PUBDEV-4567: top/bottomN speedup. Fixed overflow bug and check column type once.  PUBDEV-4567: top/bottom speedup.  Incorporate Tomas/Michal K codereview.

msm: sensor: validate the i2c table index before use  Verifying the i2c table index value before accessing the i2c table to avoid memory corruption issues.  CRs-Fixed: 1065916 Change-Id: I0e31c22f90006f27a77cd420288334b8355cee95 Signed-off-by: Sureshnaidu Laveti <lsuresh@codeaurora.org>

ASoC: msm-lsm-client: cleanup ioctl functions  Some of the ioctl command handling is not properly using the copy_from_user interface. Fix these issues and cleanup the ioctl functions to make sure there is no illegal memory access.  CRs-Fixed: 1087469 Change-Id: Ieb1beb92e7854a05b8045de0ce179d12c9a6da74 Signed-off-by: Bhalchandra Gajare <gajare@codeaurora.org>

ASoC: msm: acquire lock in ioctl  If two ioctls are triggered with different commands  there is a possibility to access freed confidence level memory. To resolve this acquire lock in ioctl. Also release mutex lock properly in error cases.  CRs-Fixed: 1103085 Change-Id: I7d6b2eff21c8297e5f0755a0c141254be32f777d Signed-off-by: Yeleswarapu Nagaradhesh <nagaradh@codeaurora.org>
